An Act relative to modernizing the pathway to becoming a certified public accountant.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 87A1/2 of chapter 112 of the General Laws, as appearing in the
2 2022 Official Edition, is hereby amended by striking subsection (e) and inserting in place thereof
3 the following subsection:-
4 (e) The educational and experience requirement for a certificate shall be one of the
5 following:
6 (i) a bachelor’s degree or its equivalent from a college or university approved by the
7 board and two years of full-time experience, or the equivalent approved by the board; or
8 (ii) a bachelor’s degree with 30 semester hours of additional education from a college or
9 university approved by the board and one of full-time experience, or the equivalent approved by
10 the board; or
